I just dont understand a libertarian (the doctrine of free will) objecting to a person's right to express a view (on any subject). I understand one's objection to my view. But not to my right to make that view. Enough on this I have made my point clear.

I start small and typically build up on a funnel approach, buying more as prices decline. That is my approach/methodlogy. I do this because of the market's volatility and the knowledge that I dont know the bottom or top. That is how I manage my risk. Sometimes it works others x.
I have my own strong views on the subject. I believe in the right of anyone to express their views on that subject or others. Very simple.
